item.title: It turns out you were right: your phone WAS listening to you
item.description: Remember when people were saying stuff like, "I think my phone is listening to me, i'm getting ads for stuff I spoke about" and people were like, "No, they're not eavesdropping on you, they're just really good at predicting your interests" ...remember that? Well, (spoiler!) it turns out that they were doing *exactly* that. Listening to your conversations and then shoveling targeted ads your way based on what you said: https://www.cbsnews.com/news/google-voice-assistant-lawsuit-settlement-68-million/ But....claimants also alleged the Google devices recorded private conversations about financial issues, personal decisions and employment. And yes, Google did that too. So many people - even Google engineers - were saying oh no, that if Google was doing this, surely some engineers would leak it. But no, apparently an L3 salary is enough to pay most people off and keep 'em quiet.

item.description: https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article220097825.html TLDR - Federal prosecutor Alexander Acosta struck a plea agreement hiding the extent of Epstein's crimes and ending an FBI investigation into whether there were more victims or more powerful people who took part. It has been called the "Deal of the Century" or a "Sweetheart Deal" Acosta was told by the Bush Administration told him to "leave it alone" because Epstein "belonged to intelligence" and was "above his paygrade." https://observer.com/2019/07/jeffrey-epstein-spy-intelligence-work/ https://www.thedailybeast.com/jeffrey-epsteins-sick-story-played-out-for-years-in-plain-sight/ Acosta resigned in July 2019 over the scandal, though he defended his actions as guaranteeing at last some jail time for Epstein. Since 2008, Epstein had been listed as a level three on the New York sex offenders register. It was a lifelong designation meaning he was considered to be at a high risk of reoffending. But Epstein maintained his properties and his assets after his conviction. After 3+1⁄2 months, He was allowed to leave the jail on "work release" for up to twelve hours a day, six days a week. This contravened the sheriff's own policies requiring a maximum remaining sentence of ten months and making sex offenders ineligible for the privilege. He was allowed to come and go outside of specified release hours. During this time, he would continue to run his child sex trafficking ring. https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article219494920.html In light of all the new information from the leaked files, this, this has me more pissed than anything else This was a miscarriage of justice!
